  <h2>Conclusion and Recommendations</h2>
  <p>
    There is no single "best" image format for every situation. Here is a quick decision framework:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Use WebP</strong> when you are optimizing images for web delivery and your audience uses modern browsers. It offers the best balance of quality and file size.</li>
    <li><strong>Use JPG</strong> when you need universal compatibility, especially for sharing photos via email, messaging, documents, or printing. It is the format that works everywhere.</li>
